defaultThere are also significant questions about their real-world
default as opposed to their theoretical efficiency.
defaultWe still don’t know enough of the details, in particular the budget and the budget-control mechanism. The sector has by far the largest potential, so
default we must expect that efforts will be made to const
defaultrain that potential through “idiosyncrasies
default” in the implementation.
defaultThermal storage is not a useful method to balance energy demand annually. The cost of a system that would buffer heat without excessive losses for a week, let alone a year, would far exce
defaulted the benefits of trying to do so.
defaultMany properties already use diurnal thermal storage. Straightforward engineering requirements drive its deployment wherever the heat-source cannot be switched on and off immediately. All that the government need do addit
defaultionally is to remove the market-skewing mechanisms that keep the value of heat relatively low compared to other forms of energy, so that larger capacity buffers may be justified where they improve the overall efficiency of the heating system.
